Here are the guidelines for spectators at Roby Friday night.

Roby has limited parking around the field and its first come first serve. The superintendent said people could bring their lawn chairs and sit along the fence to help with social distancing since the visitor stands will only hold roughly 50 people with social distancing in mind. They just implemented mask this week at school due to Fisher county having more than 20 active cases. Therefore, it is recommended to wear a mask or shield, but they will not be the PPE police.

Thanks,
Wayne Henderson
Superintendent

post_text:
The deadline to apply for P-EBT food benefits has
been extended to August 21. Did your child
receive free or reduced-price school meals
through the National School Lunch Program
during the 2019-2020 school year? If so, your
family may be eligible for this one-time food
benefit. Visit hhs.texas.gov/pebt to learn more
about P-EBT. For questions regarding eligibility or
if you need help applying, contact the P-EBT Call
Center at 833-613-6220. The public charge rule
does not apply to P-EBT benefits. If a family
thinks their child was incorrectly denied P-EBT
benefits, they need to contact HHS within 15 days
of receiving their denial notice by calling the PEBT Call Center or by email at
AES_PEBT_Complaints@hhsc.state.tx.us. They
must provide proof they received free to
reduced-price meals through the National School
Lunch Program, to get P-EBT benefits. Proof
includes the award letter that is sent to parents
when their children become eligible for the
National School Lunch Program. If children
attend a CEP or P2 school, a school ID or report
card can be used.

post_text:
Football Game Spectator Guidelines

The following recommendations are for spectators who choose to come to Mustang Stadium. Seating capacity in the stands will be limited to 50%. It will be on a first come first serve basis.

1. All spectators should self-screen prior to entering the stadium. Anyone who has

symptoms of COVID-19 should not choose to attend the games.

2. Spectators should choose to remain socially distant from one another and wear personal protective equipment while in the stands and around the commons area of the concession stand pavilion.

3. Spectators will not be allowed on the field/track before or after the game.

5. ALL Varsity Football games will be broadcasted on Mustang Nation Radio. This can be accessed by going to one of the following https://texassportsbroadcasting.com/ or through the mixlr app.

We ask for everyone`s full cooperation, so we can all make this a great season for our student athletes. If you have questions or concerns, please contact Wayne Henderson @ 940-207-0036 or Lenny Morrow @ 432-271-2148.

Thank you,

Sands CISD Administration

post_text: The Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) application is extended until August 21, 2020.P-EBT helps families get the food they need during the current pandemic by providing a one-time benefit of $285 per eligible child. While P-EBT has already issued benefits to nearly 2.8 million Texas children, there are more families that are eligible for this one-time benefit but have not submitted an application. Families can apply by submitting an application to https://yourtexasbenefits.com/Learn/PEBT (opens external link in new window) (URL is case-sensitive).

post_text:
Sands families are eligible to apply since we are a Provision 2 school district. LINK TO THE APPLICATION: https://yourtexasbenefits.com/Learn/PEBT

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit http://hhs.texas.gov/pebt or call 833-613-6220.
This product was funded by USDA.
This institution is an equal opportunity provider.

It is my pleasure to introduce Ben Loewen and his family as the 2019-2020 Sands CISD fans of the year. They did an outstanding job coming to most all of the football and basketball games whether it was in Ackerly or Abernathy. They travelled far and wide to support the Mustangs! For this we say thank you!

We want to thank the Sands Booster Club for purchasing a family pass for the Loewen’s that they can use to get in free to every home football And basketball game next school year. Thanks to Kelley Doster and the Ag department for making the sign and to Alice Sanderson for adding some final touches to the sign with the lettering. Thank you to Gandy ink for donating the t-shirts to each member of the family.

post_text: Sands CISD Class of 2020 invites you to its graduation at 8:00pm at the Sands football field on Friday, May 15th. The graduation will only allow five people per graduate to enter the visiting stands (no one will be allowed on home stands). However, that shouldn’t stop you from supporting the class of 2020. You will be allowed to park your vehicle around the field and watch the ceremony. It will also be broadcast over the radio at the FM frequency of 97.3. The radio will just be broadcast to the area around the football field. We will also stream the graduation LIVE on the Sands CISD Facebook page. A parking map will be attached to this post. Please look it over so you will see how we will enter and exit the football field. At the conclusion of the ceremony, the seniors will make their way to the front of the gym. We will exit the graduation on the backside of school and drive around forming a parade of cars that will drive by the seniors through gym parking lot and give them one last show of appreciation and congratulations for a job well done. Thanks for your support!

post_text: There have been a lot of people working hard under very “different” circumstances here at Sands CISD and these are certainly two people who fit that description. Thanks to Jana and Pascaline for getting up early and staying late as necessary to get the job done. They pumped out over 500 meals a week during the last two months and made sure they were packaged up and ready for pickup daily. Thanks for their effort and their willingness to serve! It is folks like this that makes us proud to be a part of Mustang Nation!

post_text:
Sands CISD will conduct the graduation ceremony for the Class of 2020 at 7:00pm on May 15th. The graduation will take place at the Sands CISD football stadium and will follow the graduation guidelines set forth by the State of Texas. Each graduate will be allowed 5 guests in the stands and all other spectators will park around the football field to observe the ceremony. The graduation will be locally broadcast over a radio station to allow those in attendance to hear the ceremony from their vehicle. Sands CISD will post more information such as the radio station to turn to for the broadcast and a detailed graduation schedule next week. We congratulate the Sands CISD class of 2020 and we encourage the Sands Mustang Nation to show their support on graduation night to this outstanding group of students.

Lenny Morrow
Principal
Sands CISD

post_text:
Good Afternoon!

Today the governor has closed schools for the remainder of the year. Here is the announcement on school closures.

Governor Closes Texas Schools through End of 2019-20 School Year
Gov. Greg Abbott issued several executive orders today, including one that closes all Texas schools for the remainder of the 2019-20 school year, as it "would be unsafe to allow students to gather." He noted that teachers are permitted to visit their classrooms as needed to conduct online instruction or clean out their classrooms, but should follow social distancing guidelines. Abbott said to expect more information from Commissioner of Education Mike Morath about the closures and about conducting graduation ceremonies. The statewide stay-at-home order remains in effect until April 30. Additional announcements will be made April 27.

We will continue to do "Home Based Learning" until May 15th and continue to follow the protocols we have in place.

Thanks,
Wayne Henderson
Superintendent
Sands CISD
432-353-4888 (Work)
432-353-4650 (Fax)
940-207-0036 (Cell)

Texas 1A Fan
April 9 at 3:14 PM ·

1A Senior Celebration spotlights Kaylee French from Sands High School!

Honors:
Basketball - District Champs her Senior Year for 1st time in over 10 years, Area Champs & was 1st Team All - District;
She has been a Regional Qualifier in Pole Vault, Tennis and XC throughout high school career. She has made it to state in golf and OAP. She is the senior Class President and has been a Varsity Cheerleader all 4 years. She is also a member of NHS, STUCO, FFA, BBQ team and participates in UIL.

Favorite thing to do in and out of school:
She LOVES all the things that she have been able to participate in, but basketball and OAP are her favorites. She was really starting to enjoy the BBQ team before season cut short or finger-crossed just postponed. Outside of school she loves to bake, journal, and TIKTOK!

Best thing about being from a 1A town:
The graduating class of 2020 at Sands is 6 kids. Each one is amazing! She loves being part of this close knit group, the love and support she receives from her teachers and the 6 man community, and the ability to participate in it all.

post_text:
Keeping you safe and educated is always our top priority, so we’d like to share some important facts about the coronavirus. Together we can slow the spread just by staying at home! If you must go out, stay at least 6 feet away from others, and disinfect frequently touched surfaces like countertops and doorknobs whenever you return.

Keep germs away by washing your hands with soap and water for 20 seconds. To keep from spreading germs, avoid touching your eyes, nose, or mouth and cover a cough or sneeze with your elbow. If you have symptoms of COVID-19 – a fever, dry cough, or shortness of breath – call your doctor. We hope to see you all very soon!

Parents and Staff:



By staying apart for the time being, Sands CISD is working to ensure that we are limiting the spread of COVID-19 in our community. In service of this, I want to share a one-minute video that reminds us of the most important actions we can take as individuals to reduce risk for ourselves and others: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6ZFPtFGQ8BA (opens external link in new window)



Practice social distancing

Wash your hands

Stay home as much as you can, especially if you have a cough, fever, or shortness of breath

I encourage you to watch this video with your family. And be sure to share it with family and friends on social media and via email.



Even though we are currently apart, we look forward to coming back together as a community soon.



Best,

Wayne Henderson, Superintendent

As most of you are probably aware of, the governor of Texas has closed school campuses to students to at least May 4th. This means we will continue to serve our students through distance learning. There will be another day of packet pickups on Thursday at the same times as before. 6:00 to 9:00am, 11 to 1:00pm, or 4:00 to 6:00pm. You will have an opportunity for meals to be picked up as well if you called and ordered these. If your child is sick or you are sick, please do not come to school for packet and meal pickup. We certainly want to keep everyone heathy. Thank you for your cooperation and we look forward to seeing you. Have a great day.

Lenny Morrow
Principal

post_text:
Good Afternoon!

If you haven't heard yet the Governor just shut schools down until April 3rd with a tentative start date for April 6th. We must continue to educate our students through distance learning between now and then. We will take next week to plan and develop a plan with our teachers that will give students the best opportunity to become successful with their learning. Once we have a plan set we will be in contact with you to let you know how this will work and what the expectations will be. In the mean time enjoy the time with your families and stay safe.

Thanks,
Wayne Henderson
Superintendent
Sands CISD
432-353-4888 (Work)
432-353-4650 (Fax)
940-207-0036 (Cell)

post_text:
From Mr. Henderson:
We are currently monitoring the situation with the COVID-19. TEA (Texas Education Agency) suggest exercising good judgment, applying common sense, and working closely with local health authorities to make decisions that will maximize the health and safety for student's, staff, and their families. We currently do not have any confirmed cases of the COVID-19 virus in the region. We are going to take a proactive stance and have Germ-Blast come in over spring break and do a deep cleaning of the school and buses so we are ready to come back to school Monday March 23, 2020. We wish you a safe and enjoyable spring break.

Dear Sands CISD parents,

As you probably know, there is a chance of snow and ice on Wednesday, February 5th. Any school delay will be announced by 6:00am on the day of bad weather to give everyone as much advanced notice as possible. The announcement of a weather delay will be made via the School Messenger phone call, Sands website, Sands facebook page, KBEST 95.7, News West 9 in Midland, & KLBK channel 11 in Lubbock. Thank you for your cooperation and remember to stay safe!

Lenny Morrow
Principal
Sands CISD

post_text:
I need your help! OCI Yearbook Preservation Project contacted me and would like to preserve all of Sands' yearbooks from 1950 to the present on pdf files. They will be searchable, and can be uploaded to the website. The library has all of the yearbooks except 1950, 1956-1976, 1987, 1988, 1990, and 1991. If you have any of these yearbooks, or know someone who does, I would like to borrow them for a while to send in and be scanned. This is a huge project, and OCI has given us this for free, so please get the word out!

Thank you,

Glenda Kennedy
Sands CISD
Yearbook Adviser
